//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_trigger_build}

NOTE: This operation dispatches a container build via the vessel's
{rbtgr_vessel_trigger}
using the committed
{rbtgr_build_json}
in its
{rbtgr_vessel_dir}.
All substitution values are baked at inscribe time — zero custom overrides at dispatch.

NOTE: This operation supports concurrent execution per the Concurrent Session Safety invariant.
Each invocation dispatches an independent trigger execution with a unique `BUILD_ID`.
Concurrent builds of the same vessel produce independent images with different
{rbtga_hallmark}
timestamps.

The
{rbtr_director}
dispatches a trigger-based remote container build:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtgr_vessel_dir}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL_DIR»` provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
`«INPUT_VESSEL_DIR»` is an existing directory
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_ENV_FILE»` as `«INPUT_VESSEL_DIR»/rbrv.env`
.. {rbbc_require}
`«VESSEL_ENV_FILE»` exists
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Vessel configuration not found"

//axhos_step
. *Load Vessel Configuration*:
.. Source `«VESSEL_ENV_FILE»` into current environment
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_sigil} defined and non-empty
.. {rbbc_store}
`«VESSEL_SIGIL»` from {rbrv_sigil}
.. Validate vessel directory name matches `«VESSEL_SIGIL»`
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if mismatch: "Vessel sigil does not match directory name"

//axhos_step
. *Validate Conjuring Configuration*:
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_conjure_dockerfile} defined
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_conjure_bldcontext} defined
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if missing: "Vessel not configured for conjuring"

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *Resolve Trigger Identity*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TRIGGER_NAME»` from `RBGC_RUBRIC_TRIGGER_PREFIX` + `«VESSEL_SIGIL»`
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.triggers/list[cloudbuild.triggers.list] with:
... project:
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
... location:
{rbrr_gcp_region}
... filter matching `«TRIGGER_NAME»`
.. {rbbc_require}
exactly one trigger matches
.. {rbbc_store}
`«TRIGGER_ID»` from matching trigger resource
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if not found: "Vessel trigger not found — run {rbtgo_rubric_inscribe} first"

//axhos_step
. *Dispatch Build via Trigger*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«RUBRIC_COMMIT»` as HEAD of
{rbtgr_rubric_repo}
(recorded by most recent
{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe})
.. {rbbc_submit}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.triggers/run[cloudbuild.triggers.run] with:
... project:
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
... location:
{rbrr_gcp_region}
... triggerId: `«TRIGGER_ID»`
... source.repoSource.commitSha: `«RUBRIC_COMMIT»`
.. Zero custom substitution overrides — all `_RBGY_*` values baked in
{rbtgr_build_json}
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_ID»` from response `.metadata.build.id`
.. {rbbc_show}
build dispatched with `«BUILD_ID»`
.. {rbbc_show}
Cloud Console URL for build monitoring

//axhos_step
. *Cloud Build Execution*:
.. NOTE: Build executes via OCI Layout Bridge pattern to solve BuildKit credential isolation. See Trade Study RBSOB for design rationale.
.. {gcb_service}
executes the following phases within the
{rbtgi_depot_project}:
... *Build Phase*: Multi-platform container compilation produces OCI Image Layout artifact in shared workspace. No registry credentials required.
... *Push Phase*: OCI artifact copied to
{rbtgi_repository}
using
{oauth_token}
obtained from
{gcb_service}
metadata server.
... *Platform Split Phase*: Multi-platform OCI layout split to single-platform (linux/amd64) via skopeo (per-platform tag isolation).
... *Manifest Assembly Phase*: Consumer-facing multi-platform manifest list assembled from per-platform tags.
.. All phases execute as
{rbtr_mason}
within the depot infrastructure.

//axhos_step
. *Wait for Build Completion*:
.. {rbbc_poll}
link:https://cloud.google.com/build/docs/api/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.builds/get[cloudbuild.builds.get] with:
... project:
{rbrr_depot_project_id}
... location:
{rbrr_gcp_region}
... buildId: `«BUILD_ID»`
.. Poll every 5 seconds for up to 20 minutes (240 attempts)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«BUILD_STATUS»` from response `.status`
.. Continue polling while `«BUILD_STATUS»` in [`PENDING`, `QUEUED`, `WORKING`]
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if timeout: "Build timeout after 20 minutes"
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if final status is not `SUCCESS`: "Build failed with status: «BUILD_STATUS»"

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbtga_hallmark}
. *Display Results*:
.. {rbbc_show}
build completed successfully
.. {rbbc_show}
{rbtga_hallmark}
tag (dual-timestamp: inscribe + realized)
.. {rbbc_show}
image available in
{rbtgi_repository}

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution builds the container image and stores it in the repository.
{rbtgr_provenance}
is auto-generated by Google as a signed SLSA v1.0 attestation on the built image.
Proceed to
{rbtgo_ark_about}
to assemble metadata, then
{rbtgo_ark_vouch}
to verify provenance.

==== Substitution Variable Inventory

All `_RBGY_*` substitution variables are baked into
{rbtgr_build_json}
at inscribe time by
{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}.
Cloud Build resolves these from the committed JSON — no values are overridden at dispatch.

*Vessel identity*::
[cols="1,2"]
|===
| `_RBGY_MONIKER` | Vessel sigil. Source: {rbrv_sigil}.
| `_RBGY_DOCKERFILE` | Dockerfile path relative to build context. Source: {rbrv_conjure_dockerfile}.
| `_RBGY_PLATFORMS` | Target platforms. Source: {rbrv_conjure_platforms}.
|===

*Registry coordinates*::
[cols="1,2"]
|===
| `_RBGY_GAR_LOCATION` | Artifact Registry region. Source: {rbrr_gcp_region}.
| `_RBGY_GAR_PROJECT` | Depot project ID. Source: {rbrr_depot_project_id}.
| `_RBGY_GAR_REPOSITORY` | GAR repository name. Source: {rbrr_gar_repository}.
| `_RBGY_GAR_HOST_SUFFIX` | GAR Docker host suffix. Source: RBGC constant.
| `_RBGY_ARK_SUFFIX_IMAGE` | Image artifact tag suffix. Source: RBGC constant.
| `_RBGY_CRANE_TAR_GZ` | Crane release tarball URL. Source: RBGC constant.
|===

*Provenance*::
[cols="1,2"]
|===
| `_RBGY_GIT_COMMIT` | Main repo HEAD SHA. Placeholder in generated JSON; filled at inscribe time.
| `_RBGY_GIT_BRANCH` | Main repo branch at inscribe time.
| `_RBGY_GIT_REPO` | Main repo identifier (owner/repo).
| `_RBGY_RUBRIC_REPO` | {rbtgr_rubric_repo} URL. Placeholder in generated JSON; filled at inscribe time.
| `_RBGY_RUBRIC_COMMIT` | {rbtgr_rubric_repo} HEAD SHA after push. Placeholder in generated JSON; filled at inscribe time.
| `_RBGY_INSCRIBE_TIMESTAMP` | Inscribe timestamp (`YYMMDDHHMMSS`). Placeholder in generated JSON; filled at inscribe time. Used by rbgjb01 to construct {rbtga_hallmark}.
|===

Builder image references (step `name:` fields) are resolved to digest-pinned URIs from regime pins at inscribe time.
These are inlined directly into JSON — not expressed as substitution variables.

==== Script Inlining

Step scripts (`rbgjb/*.sh`) are the source of truth for build logic.
At inscribe time,
{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
reads each script and inlines its content into the corresponding JSON `args` array.

Developers edit `rbgjb/*.sh` in the main repo, then run
{rbtgo_rubric_inscribe}
to generate
{rbtgr_build_json}
with the updated content directly into the
{rbtgr_rubric_repo}.

==== Tag Construction

Each build produces a
{rbtga_hallmark}
with dual timestamps:

`c«YYMMDDHHMMSS»-r«YYMMDDHHMMSS»`

* `c«YYMMDDHHMMSS»` — conjure mode prefix + inscribe timestamp, baked as `_RBGY_INSCRIBE_TIMESTAMP`
* `r«YYMMDDHHMMSS»` — realized timestamp, derived at build time by `rbgjb01-derive-tag-base.sh`

Example: `c260224153022-r260224160530`

Step `rbgjb01` constructs: `HALLMARK="c${_RBGY_INSCRIBE_TIMESTAMP}-r$(date -u +%y%m%d%H%M%S)"`

Complete artifact tags combine vessel moniker with {rbtga_hallmark}:

* {rbtga_ark_image}: `«MONIKER»:«HALLMARK»«ARK_SUFFIX_IMAGE»`

About and vouch artifacts are created by subsequent pipeline stages ({rbtgo_ark_about}, {rbtgo_ark_vouch}).

Multiple builds of the same inscribed JSON sort together by inscribe prefix,
each distinguished by its realized timestamp.

